The game was released for Microsoft Windows in January 2007. It is the third game in the Europa Universalis series, following Europa Universalis and Europa Universalis II. The game uses historical events and events from the period, which are sorted into five different types such as war, technology, tough decisions and events that occur at sea. The game has an extensive multiplayer mode, which allows players to compete against each other or cooperate in various ways. The game has received generally positive reviews from critics, who praised its depth and historical authenticity. The game has also spawned several expansion packs and a sequel, Europa Universalis IV, was released in 2013.
Document [2](Title: Europa Universalis series) The Europa Universalis series is a series of historical grand strategy video games made in Sweden since 2000 by Paradox Interactive. Europa Universalis is a strategy board game that takes the players through 300 years of history. Players have dozens of army and fleet units to choose from, as well as different sounds and pictures for the units. Players must gain benefits from the production of their provinces (such as building universities, workshops or forts), trade between their own provinces, and trade with Asia and the Mediterranean countries, then they have to prepare an army to conquer hostile provinces. Winning battles also depends on this phase. The strategy is made by GROFAZ (former officers of the German Reich), so the rules are very detailed. When starting each turn, one throws two dice to determine events for that turn. This might include opposition movements in their provinces, the excommunication of their leader or war declarations. The game can be won by a players by conquering a certain number of provinces, constructing wonders of the world or by collecting a certain number of ranking points (which are the battle successes, victories at key intersections and money that was collected.)
Document [3](Title: Paradox Interactive) Paradox Interactive AB is a Swedish video game publisher based in Stockholm. The company started out in 1999 as the video game division of Target Games and became an independent company in 2004. It owns the distribution company Paradox Entertainment, which publishes games from other developers as well as other forms of media related to Paradox Interactive's products. Paradox Interactive has a long history in the strategy genre, where they have published games such as the Europa Universalis series, Crusader Kings series, Hearts of Iron series, Victoria series, Cities in Motion series, and Stellaris. The company has also published a number of other games outside of the strategy genre, such as the Magicka and Cities: Skylines series. Paradox Interactive is known for its emphasis on intricate and detailed gameplay features, as well as its focus on historical accuracy in its historical strategy games.
